A gnocchi dish with a special fynd 🍄
 
#ad Here’s my creamy Spinach and Leek Gnocchi recipe using @naturesfynd Dairy-Free Chive and Onion Cream Cheese! What makes this cream cheese so special is that it includes a nutritional fungi protein, known as Fy, that’s healthy and planet-friendly! I love how much it elevates the entire dish, it’s so delicious when mixed in with some filling gnocchi and chopped greens. I urge you to try! Recipe below. 
 •
-4 tbsp butter (use vegan butter for plant based option)
-4 garlic cloves, minced
-1 leek (about 6 oz) diced and washed well
-1/2 tsp salt
-pinch of black pepper
-1 cup heavy cream (use plant based if preferred)
-3 oz spinach, roughly chopped
-4 oz Natures Fynd Dairy Free Chive and Onion Cream Cheese
-16 oz pack Gnocchi
-1/2 cup reserved gnocchi water
•
1.)Cook the gnocchi according to package directions and save ½ cup of the water. Set aside.
2.)Meanwhile, in a large skillet, melt the butter on medium heat, then add the leeks, garlic, salt and pepper. Sautee for about 10 minutes until the leeks have softened.
3.)Add in the cream and spinach and simmer another 10 minutes. The cream will thicken.
4.)Add the cream cheese and whisk well until completely melted and you have a nice creamy sauce.
5.)Add in the cooked gnocchi and the reserved water. Mix well. Season with more salt if needed. Enjoy!!
•

First recipe creation in my new kitchen with this Tomato Basil and Ricotta Orzo. 🍅🌱
•
No fancy props or backgrounds. Just real dinner making in real time with this exact song in the background. 🙂 This recipe is quick and easy and super comforting so gather your ingredients for tomorrows dinner menu. Enjoy! Recipe below. 
•
-2 tbsp olive oil 
-4 oz diced onions 
-2 large garlic cloves, minced 
-16oz pack orzo 
-1 can diced tomatoes (14 oz) 
-32 oz broth 
-2 tsp salt 
-1/2 tsp oregano 
-Pinch black pepper 
-6 oz ricotta cheese 
-1 oz freshly chopped basil 
•
1.) Heat oil and add onions and garlic. Cook for few minutes until soft. 
2.) Add in the orzo, tomatoes, seasonings and broth. Bring to a simmer and cook on low heat for about 20 minutes. Until broth is absorbed and orzo is cooked. 
3.) When done, remove from heat and add in the ricotta and basil. Mix well.

These days, there are no planned ahead recipes. Just me cooking with what I have in my fridge like this Peppery 3 Cheese Pasta because let’s face it, I always have cheese, cream and pasta on hand. What’s something you always have in your fridge or pantry?? 
Recipe below for the pasta. Enjoy! 
•
-16 oz rotini pasta 
-1 cup half half 
-2 cups heavy cream 
-2 oz Gouda cheese 
-2 oz parmesan 
-2 oz white American cheese 
-salt to taste
-1/2 cup pasta water 
-2 tbsp butter
-freshly cracked black pepper (as much as you want) 
•
1.)Cook the pasta in salted water. Reserve water.
2.) Meanwhile, in a large skillet, simmer the half half and cream for about 10 min. 
3.) Add the cheeses and melt on low another 10 min. 
4.) Add pasta water and pasta. Mix well 
5.) Add butter and top with black pepper. Add more salt if needed.

Last night, I tried to recreate a whipped feta dip we had at a local restaurant and loved so much. I didn’t measure precisely but here is what I used..
•
-8oz block of creamy feta cheese (I used @boarshead_official )
-about 4-5 big spoons of cream cheese 
-some ground black pepper 
-about 4 tbsp olive oil. (You can add more to make it creamier)
-toss everything into a blender until nice and creamy. Then top with a ton of hot honey, some chili flakes and parsley. Serve with veggies or pita.

End result from all of those tomatoes we were cutting up. One of my favorite salads that’s super easy to make and so flavorful especially when tomatoes are in season. Here is what I used to make a big bowl of it..
•
-about 2 lbs of cherry tomatoes
-1 small baguette, cut up and seasoned with salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and olive oil. Then broiled on medium for few minutes just until golden. 
-Half of a large red onion, sliced 
-4 large garlic cloves, chopped 
-A ton of fresh basil, chopped 
-about 1/3 cup olive oil 
-mix everything together and add more salt as needed. You could also add some mozzarella if you’d like. Enjoy!

ONE POT BROCCOLI CHEESE ORZO. 🥦🧀
Recipe below. 
•
•
1.)Melt 1/2 stick butter w/ 2 tbsp olive oil 
2.)Add 1 small diced onion, 1-2 minced garlic cloves, 6 cups chopped broccoli & 2 tsp kosher salt. Cook until softened. 
3.)Add 16 oz orzo, 3 cups half half or milk, 3 cups water & some black pepper. Simmer on low about 15 min or until orzo is fully cooked. If needed, add more milk or water. 
4.)Add 1 cup shredded cheddar & 1 cup shredded Parmesan. Mix well. Add more salt if needed. 
ENJOY!

It is a lifelong journey…
•

“You may not be perfect but you always do your best. You take responsibility for your mistakes. You do the inner work necessary to heal, grow and improve. You try to do better when you know better. You show up to life on your heaviest days and simply do what you can, even if you don’t feel like your most energized or “productive” self. Your efforts to learn, expand your self-awareness and persist through the tough times are commendable. You’ll always have something to work on within and outside of yourself but I hope you simultaneously acknowledge all that you are already doing to support this lifelong journey of personal development. Come to terms with the fact that you will never attain the abstract notion of “perfection” and that’s okay. That’s what makes you wondrously human. All that you ever have to offer at any given moment is your best and that will always be enough.”

•

-1 lb bag frozen broccoli 
-salt 
-4 tbsp butter 
-1 cup reserved pasta water 
-1 cup freshly grated Parmagiano Reggiano  cheese 
-salt the boiling water generously then add in the pasta and broccoli. Cook until pasta is al dente. 
-save 1 cup of the water and drain the rest. 
-add in the butter, cheese and pasta water. Mix well. Add more salt if needed.

Creamy, hidden veggie pasta your kids will not question and you only need 30 minutes to make. Recipe below. 🍅🍝
•
1.) In a large skillet, combine 
-1/4 cup olive oil 
-1 onion 
-4 garlic cloves 
-1 big can tomatoes (I use San Marzano style) 
-1 tsp salt 
-Black pepper 
-1 tsp Italian seasoning 
-1 tsp oregano 
-2 large handfuls spinach 
-1 zucchini 
And cook for about 20 min. 
2.)Transfer to a blender, add 4 oz ricotta cheese and blend until smooth. Pour back into the skillet. 
3.)Meanwhile, cook a pack of spaghetti in salted water then add the cooked pasta into the sauce with 2 tbsp butter. Mix well. Top with cheese. Enjoy!
